  <brief_title>Objective Assessment and Promotion of Physical Activity in Elderly</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Universitaire Ziekenhuizen Leuven</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Universitaire Ziekenhuizen Leuven</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of the present study is to evaluate the short-term and long-term effects of a
      cycle ergometer program on physical activity and physical fitness in elderly (65+).
      Therefore, physical activity, physical fitness and functionality are measured at baseline,
      after 10 weeks (after the intervention period), after 6 months and after 1 year.

      Different coaching techniques (to promote the use of a cycle ergometer and cycle ergometer
      program) will also be evaluated. What is the best (coaching) approach for long-term adherence
      (physical activity)?
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
